Description: The rest on the Flight into Egypt, with the Virgin and Child seated by a founatin and St Joseph pulling down a frond of a palm tree; after Correggio Engraving
Curator's comments: Agucchi was Papal delegate to Venice between 1624 and 1632; Brizio, however, died in 1623. The dedication must therefore have been added posthumously. For the very rare state before the dedication, see 1854-6-14-279.
Acquisition name: Bequeathed by: Clayton Mordaunt Cracherode (With Philipe's blindstamp and initials)
